  "prompt": "Who is Amartya Sen?",
  "response": "Amartya Sen is an Indian economist and philosopher, renowned for his work in welfare economics, social choice theory, and development economics. Born on November 3, 1933, in Santiniketan, West Bengal, India, Sen has made substantial contributions to the understanding of poverty, inequality, and human development. \n\nHe is best known for his capability approach, which emphasizes the importance of enhancing individuals' freedoms and opportunities, rather than solely focusing on economic growth or income generation. This theoretical framework has influenced development policy and practice across the globe.\n\nSen was awarded the Nobel Prize in Economic Sciences in 1998 for his contributions to welfare economics. Throughout his career, he has held numerous prestigious academic positions and has been actively involved in public discourse on issues such as social justice, democracy, and human rights. He has authored several influential books, including \"Development as Freedom\" and \"Poverty and Famines.\"\n\nIn addition to his academic achievements, Sen has served in various advisory roles for international organizations, including the United Nations. His work has been instrumental in shaping policies aimed at improving the living conditions of the world's most vulnerable populations.",
